    "kanji_explanation": "The first kanji means a very brief instant, like a blink or flash. It shows up in words such as まばたく and まばたき, where it gives the sense of something happening in the space of an eye blink. Think of it as the tiny, split-second part of an action. The second kanji means space or interval, and also the idea of between or relational place. You see it in words like まちがい and にんげん, where it contributes the sense of a gap, relation, or positioning between things; it helps form meanings about time, space, or relationships.",
